net.cloud.client.event.task.voidtasks

Interface VoidTask

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    CancellableVoidTask, CountedVoidTask, ErrorLoggingVoidTask, TextField.CursorBlinkTask, TrackingTask
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface VoidTask
    A VoidTask is some task which has no return value (void type) This is different from Task so that "return null" does not have to be included at the end of every execute method - easier lambda usage.
    Also contains default methods which take in the method used to schedule the task. These can be overridden for special scheduling behavior.
